  {
    "key": "developersPage.faq.items.0.question",
    "value": "How do I start building on Ergo?",
    "context": "FAQ content",
    "maxLength": 48
  },
  {
    "key": "developersPage.faq.items.0.answer",
    "value": "Start by learning ErgoScript fundamentals, set up the Ergo development environment (Scala/JavaScript SDKs), explore example contracts on GitHub, and join the developer Discord for support. The /learn section has structured paths for new developers.",
    "context": "FAQ content",
    "maxLength": 372
  },
  {
    "key": "developersPage.faq.items.1.question",
    "value": "What programming languages can I use for Ergo?",
    "context": "FAQ content",
    "maxLength": 69
  },
  {
    "key": "developersPage.faq.items.1.answer",
    "value": "ErgoScript is the native smart contract language. For app development, use: Scala/Java (Appkit SDK), JavaScript/TypeScript (Fleet SDK), Rust (sigma-rust), or Python (ergpy). Most developers start with Fleet SDK for web apps.",
    "context": "FAQ content",
    "maxLength": 336
  },
  {
    "key": "developersPage.faq.items.2.question",
    "value": "Is ErgoScript hard to learn?",
    "context": "FAQ content",
    "maxLength": 42
  },
  {
    "key": "developersPage.faq.items.2.answer",
    "value": "ErgoScript has a learning curve different from Solidity. It's functional and declarative rather than imperative. If you know Scala or functional programming, it's easier. The eUTXO model requires new thinking but prevents entire classes of bugs (no reentrancy).",
    "context": "FAQ content",
    "maxLength": 391.5
  },
  {
    "key": "developersPage.faq.items.3.question",
    "value": "What makes Ergo different for developers?",
    "context": "FAQ content",
    "maxLength": 61.5
  },
  {
    "key": "developersPage.faq.items.3.answer",
    "value": "Ergo offers: eUTXO model (no reentrancy attacks, predictable costs), Sigma Protocols (built-in privacy primitives), NiPoPoWs (light clients), and predictable ~$0.01 fees. Smart contracts are safer by design.",
    "context": "FAQ content",
    "maxLength": 310.5
  },
  {
    "key": "developersPage.faq.items.4.question",
    "value": "Where can I find ErgoScript code examples?",
    "context": "FAQ content",
    "maxLength": 63
  },
  {
    "key": "developersPage.faq.items.4.answer",
    "value": "Check the /patterns page for copy-paste ready contract patterns, /playbooks for step-by-step guides, and docs.ergoplatform.com for the official reference. GitHub repos of ecosystem projects provide real-world examples.",
    "context": "FAQ content",
    "maxLength": 327
  },
  {
    "key": "developersPage.faq.items.5.question",
    "value": "Are there grants for Ergo developers?",
    "context": "FAQ content",
    "maxLength": 55.5
  },
  {
    "key": "developersPage.faq.items.5.answer",
    "value": "Yes! The Ergo Foundation offers grants for open-source projects, dApps, tooling, and research. Apply via GitHub or join the developer community to discuss your project first.",
    "context": "FAQ content",
    "maxLength": 261
  },
